\b \cf0 Explorer Component Navigation
\b0 \
- Tab / Shift-Tab focus will start on the structure object identifier (on "QTE-1155" in the title "For Quote QTE-1155")\
- Tab will be circular between the structure object ID, the first node of the tree and the action on the Explorer action bar (Add and Remove). \'a0Users will use arrow keys to navigate the structure itself.\
- When the Add (by Type-in) panel is open the type input, short description input, commit and cancel elements will also be included in the Tab / Shift-Tab navigation\
\
\

\b Structure Navigation
\b0 \
- Users can single click on a node in the structure to view the details of the selected object in the object details pane.\
- When focus is on the structure the following keyboard navigation will be supported\
\'a0\'a0-- Arrow down moves focus down tree\
\'a0\'a0-- Arrow up moves focus up tree\
\'a0\'a0-- Arrow right will expand a parent node with focus\
\'a0\'a0-- Arrow left will collapse a parent node with focus\'a0\
\
\

\b Structure Node Selection
\b0  \'a0\
- Single click on a node in structure\
- Shift+Click will do a contiguous selection of structure values\'a0\
- Ctrl+Click will toggle select non-contiguous structure values\'a0\
- Shift+Arrow Up/Down will do a contiguous selection of structure values\
\
\

\b Editing a Structure Node
\b0 \
- Double click on node will allow user to modify the short description of the object\
- Enter on node when it has focus will allow user to modify the short description of the object\
\
